relevant_findings.general: Distress, diaphoretic and cool. Frequent belching. Alert and oriented x3.
relevant_findings.heent: Normocephalic/atraumatic. EOMI. PERRL. Mucous membranes pink and moist.
relevant_findings.cardiovascular: Elevated heart rate (110-120 bpm), regular rhythm, no murmurs/rubs/gallops. Very pronounced heart sounds.
relevant_findings.lungs: Clear to auscultation. Cannot take deep breaths without pain on inspiration.
relevant_findings.abdomen: Moderately rigid (guarding) and distended, diffuse tenderness primarily on left side (middle and lower quadrants). Unable to palpate deeply due to pain and nausea. Audible bowel sounds.
relevant_findings.extremities: Warm, well perfused. Normal strength and bulk bilaterally.
relevant_findings.neurological: GCS 15. Cranial nerves II-XII grossly intact.
